# FitClub project rules

## UI (all new frontend UI)

- **Colors**: `bg-neutral-50` / `bg-background` and `text-neutral-900` / `text-primary-500` (or RN: `theme.colors.background`, `theme.colors.text`, `theme.colors.primary`). Never use raw hex, rgb, or named colors in components.
- **Spacing**: Use the spacing scale only (e.g. `theme.spacing.sm`, `theme.spacing.md`; or Tailwind `p-4`, `m-2`). No arbitrary padding/margin.
- **Radius**: Use border radius tokens only (`theme.radius.sm/md/lg` or `rounded-sm/md/lg`). No arbitrary values.
- **No inline styles**: Prefer StyleSheet + theme (RN) or Tailwind utility classes; never inline style objects with hex or magic numbers.

See `.cursor/rules/ui-design-tokens.mdc` for the full rule.

## Future features and NFRs (think when planning)

When planning features, storage, or infrastructure, consider the rules in `.cursor/rules/future-features-and-nfrs.mdc`:

- **AI workout logging**: Gemini/Claude to simplify workout entry; always account for AI cost.
- **Media**: MVP = no user picture uploads. Post-MVP = activity pictures allowed; requires extra storage and cost.
- **Database and infra**: DB can grow exponentially with workout logs. Design for cost, High Availability, Disaster Recovery, scalability, and performance NFRs.

## Reference codebase: TeenLifeManager (read-only)

**Do not modify any file in the TeenLifeManager folder from this workspace.** TeenLifeManager is included for reference only. You may read and copy from it (structure, patterns, docs); never edit, move, or delete files in that project.
